#: ../../../prop_tgt/Swift_PACKAGE_NAME.rst:2
msgid "Swift_PACKAGE_NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_tgt/Swift_PACKAGE_NAME.rst:6
msgid "Specify the Swift package name for a target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_tgt/Swift_PACKAGE_NAME.rst:8
msgid ""
"This property sets the package name passed to the Swift compiler via the ``-"
"package-name`` flag, which enables the package access control in Swift code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_tgt/Swift_PACKAGE_NAME.rst:14
msgid ""
"Package access control was added in Swift 5.8 and Xcode 15. This target "
"property has no effect when using an earlier version of Swift or Xcode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_tgt/Swift_PACKAGE_NAME.rst:17
msgid ""
"If the property is not set, the :variable:`PROJECT_NAME` variable is used as "
"the default package name.  See policy :policy:`CMP0216`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_tgt/Swift_PACKAGE_NAME.rst:20
msgid ""
"Setting this property to the empty string will result in the target being "
"compiled without a package name."
msgstr ""
